# Intelligent Land Cover Classification and Environmental Reporting System

## Overview

This project presents an end-to-end intelligent system for land cover classification using Sentinel-2 multispectral satellite imagery. The system combines Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), spectral feature engineering, Large Language Models (LLMs), and an interactive Streamlit application to provide automated environmental analysis and reporting.

The project evaluates three different image representations:

* RGB Images
* NDVI (Normalized Difference Vegetation Index)
* RGB + NIR (Near Infrared)

The final system classifies land cover types and generates professional environmental reports with recommendations using a Groq-powered LLM.

---

## Features

* Land cover classification using CNNs
* Comparison of RGB, NDVI, and RGB+NIR representations
* NDVI-based vegetation analysis
* Automated environmental report generation using LLMs
* Interactive Streamlit interface
* Sentinel-2 TIFF image support
* Confidence-based model comparison

---

## Dataset

### Dataset Download

The EuroSAT Multispectral Dataset can be downloaded from Zenodo:

Dataset URL:

https://zenodo.org/records/7711810/files/EuroSAT_MS.zip?download=1


### EuroSAT Multispectral Dataset

The project uses the EuroSAT Multispectral Dataset based on Sentinel-2 satellite imagery.

Dataset Characteristics:

* 10 Land Cover Classes
* 13 Spectral Bands
* Sentinel-2 Satellite Images
* Multispectral TIFF Format

Classes:

1. AnnualCrop
2. Forest
3. HerbaceousVegetation
4. Highway
5. Industrial
6. Pasture
7. PermanentCrop
8. Residential
9. River
10. SeaLake

---

## Data Representations

### RGB

Uses visible bands:

* Red
* Green
* Blue

Input Shape:

```text
64 × 64 × 3
```

---

### NDVI

Vegetation index calculated using:

NDVI = (NIR - Red) / (NIR + Red)

Input Shape:

```text
64 × 64 × 1
```

---

### RGB + NIR

Uses:

* Red
* Green
* Blue
* Near Infrared

Input Shape:

```text
64 × 64 × 4
```

---

## CNN Architecture

All experiments use the same CNN architecture to ensure fair comparison.

```text
Input Layer
    ↓
Conv2D (32, 3×3, ReLU)
    ↓
Batch Normalization
    ↓
MaxPooling2D (2×2)
    ↓
Conv2D (64, 3×3, ReLU)
    ↓
Batch Normalization
    ↓
MaxPooling2D (2×2)
    ↓
Conv2D (128, 3×3, ReLU)
    ↓
Batch Normalization
    ↓
MaxPooling2D (2×2)
    ↓
Flatten
    ↓
Dense (128, ReLU)
    ↓
Dropout (0.5)
    ↓
Dense (10, Softmax)
```

---

## Training Configuration

* Optimizer: Adam
* Batch Size: 32
* Early Stopping
* Model Checkpoint
* ReduceLROnPlateau
* Sparse Categorical Crossentropy

---

## Results

| Model       | Test Accuracy |
| ----------- | ------------: |
| NDVI CNN    |        90.79% |
| RGB CNN     |        95.19% |
| RGB+NIR CNN |        96.27% |

### Key Finding

The RGB+NIR model achieved the highest accuracy, demonstrating that Near Infrared information provides valuable spectral features for land cover classification.

---

## LLM-Based Environmental Reporting

The system integrates a Groq-hosted Large Language Model to generate professional environmental reports.

### Pipeline

```text
Input TIFF Image
        ↓
RGB CNN
NDVI CNN
RGB+NIR CNN
        ↓
Predictions + Confidence Scores
        ↓
NDVI Statistics
        ↓
Groq LLM
        ↓
Environmental Report
        ↓
Recommendations
```

The generated report includes:

* Classification Summary
* Confidence Analysis
* Vegetation Assessment
* Environmental Interpretation
* Potential Risks
* Recommendations

---

## Streamlit Application

The project includes an interactive Streamlit application that allows users to:

* Upload Sentinel-2 TIFF images
* Run all CNN models
* View prediction confidence
* Analyze NDVI statistics
* Generate environmental reports
* Download generated reports

---

## Installation

Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone <repository-url>
cd project
```

Install dependencies:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Set your Groq API key:

```bash
set GROQ_API_KEY=your_api_key
```

---

## Run Streamlit Application

```bash
streamlit run app.py
```

